to the editor re the impact of health care reviews editorial may 1 you cite the suggestion of congressional conferees that only published academic articles or other reliable evidence be considered by medical review boards when deciding the necessity of a treatment medicine is only part science it is art based on science whenever pertinent evidence is available a scientific study seldom proves that a given doctor 's judgment for an individual patient is right or wrong but there is evidence of a different sort it 's called clinical experience for example some doctors prescribed certain oral contraceptives for acne although there was no evidence until one clever drug company collected the cases to prove it clinical experience includes new and prior studies along with knowledge of people physiology and pharmacology it is called the art of medicine pepi granat md south miami fla may 1 2000

